getURI

public static java.lang.String getURI(java.lang.String resource,
                                      java.lang.String... attrs)
Returns the specified URI. This is done by appending the resource URI to the base URI. If there are parameters in the URI, those are replaced using the provided attrs.

Parameters:
resource - Resource string (Res constants should be used).
attrs - Arbitrary number of URI attribute replacements (should match the number of attributes marked with curly braces).
Returns:
Processed URI string
